  0 0x00000000 0x00000000 2047 2047         ascii Terrain descriptions\r\n\t\r\nTropical\r\n\r\n*Tees\r\nWarm ocean breezes and an open, level hitting area make this the "only" place to be when starting a hole.  \r\n*Green\r\nWatered, fed, and maintained to exacting standards; welcomes well-placed approach shots (press <tab> for tricky green).        \r\n*Sand Trap\r\nModerately difficult hazard that tests players' course management abilities  (press <tab> to rotate).\r\n*Rough\r\nDense, shaggy grass (2-3" in height) inhibits roll and deadens bounce.  Tough to make solid contact out of this cabbage.\r\n*Pot Bunker\r\nAn open sand pit where poorly-hit shots go to die.  Players need divine intervention from the golf gods to get back into play. \r\n*Stream\r\nEasier to climb every mountain than to try and ford this stream.  Scores take a bath along with the ball; take one penalty stroke.       \r\n*Water\r\nThe Bermuda Triangle of hazards.  Players finding themselves at the bottom of this well may want to send out a search party.    \r\n*Tropical Bush\r\nRecovery skills and lots of luck required to get away from this fruity stuff (press <tab> to size).\r\n*Tropical Tree\r\nPlayers hitting into this wood best hope for a lucky bounce.  Green and tangled and unforgiving (press <tab> to size).\r\n*Palm Tree\r\nGolfers trying to get past these tropical delights might consider prayer as an option to a mid-iron (press <tab> to size).  \r\n*Fairway\r\nA closely cut and well-tended waystation between tee and green.  Shots roll long and bounce high.\r\n*Firm Fairway\r\nJust like your old, familiar fairway, but with more "zip".  Provides more roll, higher bounce, and tighter lie than a traditional fairway.\r\n*Deep rough\r\nUnkempt grasses that are merciless on shots that stray from the fairway.  Recovery shots out of deep rough tend to squirt and fly.  "FORE!"\r\n*Waste bunker\r\nTwo hazards for the price of one: nasty brush jutting out of a coarse sand bed.  Stuff of golf nightmares.  \r\n*Brush\r\nTwisted and thorny low brush.  Has been known to reduce players to sobbing heaps.\r\n*Rocks\r\nBlack lava puncuates the otherwise lush green lands
